{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"84123afa-08c5-4c5c-86bf-13ddc6c82b41","content":"With xUnit v3 + MTP, the VSTest filter syntax changes. Here's the translation:\n\n**Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP / xUnit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&trait=Category%3DSmoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences with MTP:\n\n| VSTest syntax | MTP syntax |\n|---|---|\n| `Category=Smoke` | `trait=Category%3DSmoke` |\n| `&` (AND) | `&` (same) |\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` | `FullyQualifiedName~X` (same) |\n\nMTP doesn't have a built-in `Category` property — traits are accessed via the generic `trait` filter with the format `trait=Name%3DValue` (where `%3D` is URL-encoded `=`).\n\nAlternatively, you can use the non-encoded form with quoting depending on your shell:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nWould you like me to verify this runs against your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9e31e77b-4285-4915-9eaa-3715d37ec370","outputTokens":315,"requestId":"6817:1F9B94:745170:7BD239:6A044DC8"},"id":"aace286d-2e5d-4b75-b638-f9c6e7e16cfe","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:09:21.422Z","parentId":"825cda1f-fb49-46e7-ac45-18fbbae8c43f"}
